The Silicon Photonics Packaging Design (SPPD) team has an Intel Contract Employee (ICE) opening for a Thermal engineer. Key responsibilities include performing thermal-characterizations of packages, developing test plans, and post-processing the collected data. 
In this position, the candidate will be responsible for lab collaterals and tools required for testing units, recording and analyzing thermal-mechanical data, making calculations and estimates, and reporting their findings. As part of the job function, the employee will work in a team environment and interact with peers and also define and implement lab experiments for feasibility and validation of newly developed engineering concepts. 
This position is not eligible for Intel immigration sponsorship. 
Qualifications 
Minimum Qualifications
 BS in Mechanical Engineering or related disciplines with 3+ years of relevant experience 
1+ years of relevant experience in the areas of thermal and system development and validation 
1+ years of in DOE planning and execution, particularly lab scale thermal measurements 
1+ years of experience in statistical analysis and reliability analysis using JMP or similar software 
1+ years of experience in mechanical design tools (for example, SolidWorks or similar CAD tools) 
Preferred Qualifications 
1+ years of relevant experience in heat transfer and semiconductor packaging 
Experience in LabVIEW software 
Experience in NI DAQ systems and common DAQ/computer interfaces for performing thermal and flow tests in the lab 
Experience in common thermal and fluids analysis software (ANSYS, ANSYS Icepak, etc) 
Experience in project management, particularly in semiconductor packaging 
Experience with machining, electronics, fabrication, power tools, hand tools, and soldering 
